snippet.textDisplay:
Hes an actor. Hes acting- a very popular character at that..one that was brutally ruthless. Almost like a reintroduction to a possiblity of future episodes (like his character never died).
Its possible that spacey is simply trying to get his career back on track...
...and the issues in his personal life just adds to the realism of the character..making the observer draw the parallels (which is not hard to do, which people saw initially and through events, grew stronger).
Overidentifying the character with the actor is probably really normal for him (from his fans)...
And while it might seem creepy because its too similar, from his perspective, he might see himself as nothing like his character, so to do this bit is a contrast. (Like , my character would do this, not me).
However, with the publics blurred lines between actor and character, you have to be realistic about how it might be recieved.
A lot of people do not dance around the elephant as a means to reingage, they quietly pick a new way to reinvent themselves..
But most people arent famous either, and thats gotta be hard to do after becoming infamous.
I mean, he could have done no bit..just him as an actor by a fire, asking for kindness to one another (without the nefarious, add on dialogue), and how would that have gone over?
(I really dont know)
But i dont think that was the point..it was not a personal message, just acting set in a personal message SCENE.

And identifying as an 'anti actor' (an actor that refuses acting as a healthful means of expession), i can understand why he might choose to do this bit regardless of public reception-
Acting, for a lot of artists are a way to express energy (aspects of themselves, aspects they discover in themselves, or pure bliss of escapism through a character).

The guy is an actor, this is what he does..telling him not to act is like telling him not to breath..
Buy the pr manager that green lighted this bit?
If it were me, i would have hesitated at the idea..
Thats some serious trust there(if this bit was in fact a pr idea).
Everything about this bit says no:
1. The timing (in relation to his personal life)
2. the topic
3.the chosen character
4. The implication
5. The setting (xmas religious themed)
But maybe they know something i dont..im not in pr..i also dont desire to keep my acting career going..
Jumping on the infamy to keep a buzz generated??

Fame bites you in the ass everytime, everywhere, no matter how you slice it.

snippet.textDisplay:
I see many people calling him a molester and a murderer, but where's the proof?
Why are people convicting him of the crimes which he MAY didn't even commit?
What I feel is the #MeToo movement has its merits as well as demerits and one of the main demerits is people started accusing celebrities without any evidence and yet the celebrities lose their job, respect, and fame because of it.
Again I am not saying that he didn't do or he did it, my opinion is that it is not right to convict a person in our mind just because he/ she had been accused of something. There's a difference between the accused and a convict.
